 YOU HATE ME _ YOU REALLY HATE ME  &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ There seems to be so much anger in the air these
days.
</P>
<P>
   I vaguely sensed hostility directed my way this morning as I was
driving to work on the sidewalk in my Ford Exploitation stretch
SUV, chatting on my cell phone, smoking a cigarette, drinking a
beer, cleaning my handgun, blaring a new gangsta-rap CD and lookin'
good in my sweatshop-made, baby-sealskin Dodger jacket.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe it's my ``No fat chicks'' bumper sticker. People take
stuff so literally.
</P>
<P>
   THEN THERE'S the guy that Yana Murphy spotted driving south on
101, stuck in a big jam due to an accident.
</P>
<P>
   The guy and Yana both exit at Third St., and she watches him cut
across two lanes and zoom back onto the freeway, leapfrogging about
50 cars.
</P>
<P>
   The guy's license plate: 4ETHIX.
</P>
<P>
   THE BANDITO in ``Treasure of the Sierra Madre'' was wrong when
he told Humphrey Bogart, ``We don't need any stinking bodges.''
</P>
<P>
   You  &UR; do  &LR; need stinking bodges. It's just that they don't have to
be  &UR; real  &LR; stinking bodges.
</P>
<P>
   Undercover investigators testing security at 19 sensitive U.S.
federal buildings got into all 19 using phony badges.
</P>
<P>
   In a related story, White House guards let a man slip past
security wearing an ``Official Bikini Inspector'' T-shirt, but it
was OK because he was the president.
</P>
<P>
   WOW, A RARE four-bagger at Hallidie Plaza Thursday!
</P>
<P>
   Both escalators between the Muni-BART station and the sidewalk
were out of order, as usual. And so was the handicapped elevator.
</P>
<P>
   That left the stairway, which was completely blocked, top and
bottom, with a dozen S.F. DPW sawhorses, though nobody was doing
any work on the stairs.
</P>
<P>
   Man, it's a bad day when the stairs break down.
</P>
<P>
   People were climbing over the sawhorses _ it looked like a
senior citizens' hurdles race.
</P>
<P>
   The sight reminded me of that old TV commercial where O.J.
Simpson is sprinting through an airport, hurdling luggage.
</P>
<P>
   Which now seems, I don't know, disturbing.
</P>
<P>
   SO IT'S ONE, two, three, what are we fightin' for? Country Joe
McDonald still hasn't figured that out, but he has created a plaque
with the names of all 163 San Franciscans who died in the Vietnam
War, and hopes to find a home for the plaque soon.
</P>
<P>
   And on Memorial Day, the 163 will be remembered in many ways,
including: a free lunch at John's Grill for immediate families of
the 163, space permitting. Call (415) 777-4700.
</P>
<P>
   AT CHAPEL of the Chimes, a cemetery/mortuary/crematorium in
Oakland, Lil Arnerich noticed the signs, ``Customer Parking Only.''
</P>
<P>
   Lil (yes, a man named Lil) said to his wife, Norma, ``Shouldn't
that be `Visitors'?''
</P>
<P>
   COW HOLLOW changed a lot when the cows packed up and left, but
it's still changing.
</P>
<P>
   One morning this week, Marina Costabile took a stroll and
noticed:
</P>
<P>
   The Jack in the Box on Lombard closed down (OK, no major
tragedy).
</P>
<P>
   The venerable Thriftway market on Buchanan is going out of
business after 35 years run by the same family (``It's time to
go,'' owner John Moresco said Thursday).
</P>
<P>
   Bepples Pies is going bye-bye. The clerk told folks he was about
to sell the very last Bepples apple pie ever.
</P>
<P>
   BAD NEWS: A thief drove off with a large mail truck that was
parked, keys in ignition, behind the mail-processing plant on
Bryant.
</P>
<P>
   Good news: Postal officials, still searching for the truck, say
the heist shouldn't affect the time it takes to deliver that mail.
(Just kidding!)
</P>
<P>
   I hope the postal worker who left that rig unattended wasn't one
of those rude people who leave the gas tank on E.
</P>
<P>
   CANDIDATE for the NRA's ``innovative usage'' award: the
68-year-old Red Bluff man who removed a corn from his foot with a
.22 rifle. He also removed a toe.
</P>
<P>
   Good thing it wasn't a pimple on his nose.
</P>
<P>
   BILL CLINTON, hustling up support for the big China trade bill,
offered to play golf with key representatives in return for their
votes.
</P>
<P>
   When it comes to horse tradin', Bill makes the Hearst execs look
like rubes.
</P>
<P>
   AND REMEMBER, if you don't overreact, you run the risk of having
to  &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
