<P>
   LATHAM-COLUMN _ MARSHALL, Texas _ A guy came by my office a
while back with a problem. It was his wife. This leaves the
possibilities wide open, I know. For a fact, if you are female and
were to switch the word ``wife'' and put in ``husband'' the range
of problems could stretch forever. (Latham, Marshall News
Messenger). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ ``Good evening, folks. My name is LaPierre. I'll
be your hunter and gatherer this evening. Have you dined at Chez
NRA before? No? Well, first let me welcome you. I see you've
already been to our store. May I say, madam, that that Gucci ammo
belt is just stunning on you.'' (Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED
THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ PARIS _ I am sitting in a Paris restaurant
watching American tourists (and myself) fumbling with how to hold a
knife and fork while eating. We don't do it the same way as
Europeans but we make fools of ourselves trying. (Kleinberg, Cox
News Service.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ The Bible tells us that God labored
for six days of creation and rested on the seventh. Historians tell
us the ancient Jews took the idea of the week from the Babylonians,
who lived on the site of modern-day Iraq. (Andy Glass is a
columnist for Cox News Service in the Washington bureau.) MOVED
THURSDAY.
</P>
