<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Caladiums were actually having a
little renaissance in the 1950s, and then they seem to have
disappeared for a while, at about the same time so many families
moved to the suburbs, to large but relentlessly sunny gardens;
caladiums do best in dappled shade. Now that trees have grown up in
the suburbs, caladiums are coming back. By Marty Ross.
</P>
