<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUTO-TOYOTA-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     COMPACT COROLLA IS BEST-SELLING AUTO 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   What is the world's best-selling car ever?
</P>
<P>
   Most of us have a favorite or two we think ought to be on that
list, but to make such a list, the car would have to be a
mass-market vehicle rather than just a niche car such as the
Chevrolet Corvette, America's sports car.
</P>
<P>
   Some good guesses would be the Ford Mustang, Chevrolet Cavalier,
Chevrolet Bel Air, (the original) Chevy Nova or even the Ford
Taurus.
</P>
<P>
   But the winner, in a news flash announced recently by Toyota, is
the compact Toyota Corolla.
</P>
<P>
   And the car it unseated as the world's best-selling car of all
time is one that we all perhaps should have guessed: the Volkswagen
Beetle.
</P>
<P>
   To date, since introduction in 1966, there have been more than
24 million Corollas sold worldwide. And that doesn't include about
a million Corollas made at the New United Motor Manufacturing Inc.
plant in Fremont, Calif., which were labeled as Geo Prizm,
Chevrolet Prizm or Chevy Nova (the later version).
</P>
<P>
   That compares with about 23 million Beetles sold (not counting
the New Beetle, which is a completely different animal).
</P>
<P>
   Sales of the original Beetle were discontinued about 1977 in the
United States, but production and sales of the vehicle continue in
South America, and that car was built and sold in Mexico into the
mid-90s.
</P>
<P>
   Its demise in the United States came as a result of safety and
anti-smog requirements that would have been too expensive and
impractical to meet.
</P>
<P>
   Toyota hasn't had that problem with the Corolla, which has been
continually upgraded over the years.
</P>
<P>
   The latest generation, the 2001 model, is arriving at U.S.
dealerships now, and it has been extensively restyled.
</P>
<P>
   It's not a real exciting car to have as the world's all-time
best-seller, but it has been a very good car over the years _ one
that people have come to depend on for long-term, dependable and
affordable transportation. And in the long run, those attributes
are the ones that really count with consumers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
