<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; ATTENTION EDITORS: A ``separate-buy'' interview with Riccardo
Muti, described below, has moved in the ``a'' and ``e'' news
files. &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COURTING MUTI, THE MAESTRO OF MILAN
</P>
<P>
   NYPHILHARMONIC-MUTI-INTERVIEW _ Will Riccardo Muti, the
58-year-old music director of La Scala, take on one of the most
coveted jobs in America's classical-music scene _ that of music
director for the New York Philharmonic? ``There are strong
possibilities I will sign,'' says Muti in an interview. By Kelly
Burke.
</P>
<P>
   To purchase the story, contact one of the following New York
Times Syndicate sales representatives:
</P>
<P>
   --U.S. and Canada: DEBRA WEYDERT in New Jersey at
1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697.
</P>
<P>
   --Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942.
</P>
<P>
   --Latin America: ANA PENA in New York, 212-499-3333; fax,
212-499-3382.
</P>
</TEXT>
