<P>
   AIDS-MEDICARE (WASHINGTON) _ Rep. Tom A. Coburn is pushing a
bill to eliminate the two-year period that many AIDS victims must
wait for Medicare benefits that cover drug therapies. Advocates for
people with HIV/AIDS are applauding the measure, which Coburn
introduced Thursday. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPBELL-DOCTORS (WASHINGTON) _ Rep. Tom Campbell, R-Calif.,
says he is ``outraged'' at House Speaker J. Dennis Hastert's
decision Thursday to yank from floor consideration Campbell's bill
that would give self-employed doctors the right to bargain
collectively with health insurance companies. Campbell, who is
running for the Senate against incumbent Dianne Feinstein,
D-Calif., insists his measure has enough support to pass despite a
vote Wednesday among House Republicans to keep it from coming to a
vote. By JUDY HOLLAND.
