</P>
<P>
   BUSH-COMMENCEMENT (Crawford, Texas) _ For the 45-member Class of
2000 at Crawford High School, graduation night truly was a night to
remember. At commencement on the football field, the speaker was
their new neighbor, Gov. George W. Bush. Now that the governor has
a home here, this ranching area near Waco might be the site of the
next summer White House _ if the presumptive Republican nominee has
his way. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-GUNS (Austin, Texas) _ On the anniversary of the passage
of the state's concealed handgun law, state Sen. Jerry Patterson,
who sponsored the legislation, talks about the ``success'' of his
measure, while Texans Against Gun Violence rail against it. By
KATHY WALT.
