   WORKING-COLUMN (Undated) _ Two years ago, the White House
threatened to veto a bill that would increase the number of
high-skilled work visas available unless U.S. workers were given
first crack at the jobs and weren't laid off to make room for
immigrants. The protections were added, the visa limits were raised
and President Clinton signed the bill into law _ but companies
don't have to abide by it. By L.M. SIXEL.
