occupation in southern Lebanon ended, the boundaries of the
oft-turbulent Middle East has changed. But is it for the better?
Members of the South Lebanon Army, accused of brutality by human
rights groups and financially backed by Israel, now find themselves
unarmed and at the mercy of their own countrymen. Hezbollah, the
``Party of God'' that has raged a terrorist campaign to repel the
Israeli occupation, is emboldened by victory. And Israeli citizens,
too many of whom never backed the occupation in the first place,
now worry that their Lebanese neighbors might seek retaliation.
Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
