shot and killed a seventh-grade language teacher in a classroom
Friday during the last period on the final day of classes, police
said. By Jon Nordheimer.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   GORE-BRADLEY (Washington) _ In the more than two months since
Vice President Al Gore vanquished former Sen. Bill Bradley in the
Democratic presidential primaries, the two men have not spoken. But
there are signs there may soon be a rapprochement. Aides to Bradley
say they expect the him to appear with Gore sometime before the
Democratic convention in August, and possibly as soon as next
month. By James Dao. (450 words)
</P>
