<P>
   SUMMER-FILMS (Undated) _ Like death and taxes some things never
seem to change. Like summer movies. Always the same: fiery
explosions, knock-out special effects, thin plots, well-muscled
stars. Add to that nonstop television commercials, toys on the
shelves, action figures in the Happy Meal. It seems so formulaic.
Despite appearances, however, the summer blockbuster has changed
plenty since its birth, but the changes have been subtle and
cumulative. By Nancy Hass.
</P>
<P>
   LOCATIONS-FILMS (Paris) _ Romantic confusions of person and
place: Films like ``The Talented Mr. Ripley,'' ``The Beach,'' ``Out
of Africa,'' ``The Sheltering Sky'' and the recently released ``I
Dreamed of Africa'' have attempted to explore what happens when
people join hands and parachute into the wilderness of a shared
dream. Those who chase their fantasies to Paris or Kenya, Thailand
or Morocco usually learn that dreams are promises waiting to be
broken: love in a new climate withers as often as it blooms. By
Kristin Hohenadel.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THEATER &LR;
