<P>
   MICROSOFT (Washington) _ Paul Allen and Steve Ballmer would be
able to own shares in both companies created by the government's
latest proposal to split Microsoft in two. But Bill Gates couldn't.
The final revision of the government's proposed remedy in the
Microsoft antitrust suit would allow the Microsoft chairman to own
a stake in only one of the new companies. His co-founder _ Allen _
and close friend and chief executive _ Ballmer _ could invest in
either or both because of changes made in the proposal by the
government's attorneys over the past two days.
</P>
