<P>
   &QL; 
TRIPLETS _ Doctors deliver triplets too early, resulting in more
health problems for babies and higher hospital bills, according to
a new report by the Valley's premier multiple-births specialist.
Mothers of triplets are pleading with doctors to deliver them at 30
or 31 weeks because they are getting so large and are in such
discomfort, Dr. John Elliott told the American College of
Obstetricians and Gynecologists this week. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
HOUSING _ Builders around Arizona are still building apartments
that are not accessible for the disabled despite requirements that
have been around for a decade, Attorney General Janet Napolitano
said Friday. Napolitano has slapped 21 new or nearly new apartment
and condominium complexes around the state with ``administrative
charges'' for such problems as ramps that are too steep for
wheelchairs to climb or doorways too narrow to pass through. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
